comment:
Fermented at 58F for 4 days, then brought to 70F to clean up.  Crashed to 32F and added glycerin.
SG of 1.060 right on the freaking money.  (figured out a single batch sparge is better).  
FG of 1.012 again... right on the money.  I blame my good attenuation on oxygenation.  
Pumpkin pie spice was not *quite* enough IMO initially.  Added 1/2tsp after 1 week.
